<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>1 item loot limit?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?holydevil">holydevil</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 4:18 p.m. 22/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> 1 item loot limit?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I got into a little scruff with some upstart that thought it would be nice time to fight me after I got finished killing monsters, he is dead now kinda why I like Pvp to take losers out or bullies. But when i went to loot him I could not take more than one item? why is this? is that the limit? their gold, and one item? That stinks when I start killing CC left and right I am gonna barely make any money out of it. =o(

<BR>no but seriously am I doing something wrong or is this a game rule thing.
<P>Which brings me to another thing....
<BR>If so I think it should not happen not saying thee should not be a limit on items, maybe there should I personally feel they shouldn't but what gets to me is when I get berated by some ( GM's) about being OOC when they bring in these OOF rules in OOG: out of fantasy rules into play.) I mean instead of haveinf this -/+4 level thing whee I just can't swing at some newbie is wierd. I think instead why dont they have it wer you get the worst repuatiton and eventually are not let in any towns that might make life hard. It think it would sound bad a high level guy killing low level people would be like dishonorable preying on the weak, not many towns would like that
<P>thats it
<BR>HolyDevil
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
